<br>
Instead of new spells, focus items or critical spell hits how about just increasing the base mana regen rate across the board at all levels for all classes that use mana, making it stackable with all mana regen increasing spells and items? This should be done on a percentage basis meaning take whatever your mana regen rate is for your level now and increase it X percent, maybe 20 percent as an example. Lower level people will get only a few more mana per tick while high level people will get much more. This seems to me to be a good way to distribute it evenly throughout the levels and it certainly beats giving people over level 50 something like 1 more mana per tick which isn't even noticable. Also this will benefit everyone, not just those lucky enough to be in uber guilds who can raid high end mobs which are likely to be the ones dropping focus items. I am not sure I really like the idea of magicians being able to summon great focus items either because then it'll put too much dependence on them like EQ already has on enchanters.<br>
<br>
My reasoning behind this idea is simple, less downtime. It helps in groups because we will be able to cast more times in a fight and sitting less, thus more damage. Then maybe people will actually invite many of the caster classes to groups more if they think we are actually contributing instead of sitting on our butts all the time. Of course the side effect of this is that it will make soloing faster too. To that I say so what? Most higher level casters who can solo would prefer to not be soloing anyway, I know I'm sure sick of it. I do not think any idea that can help casters in groups should be discounted just because it makes them better at soloing, otherwise nothing will ever get done.<br>
<br>
In my opinion there is way too much downtime in EQ, to med a full bar of mana takes more than 10 minutes without any kind of mana regen enchancing spells. Downtime is boring whether it be in a group or solo. This lets us do more damage by casting an extra few spells in a battle rather then making us do significantly more in one blast, which would just mean more agro and wasted mana for the healers saving us. I suggest this for all classes that use mana so its fair, perhaps giving the classes that need it more a bigger increase. In my opinion the high end game has become rediculously overdependent on enchanters and this has had the negative result of exp groups consisting basically of a warrior, cleric, monk/rogue and enchanter with some other melee type thrown in to fill out the group. Enchanters will still be needed and wanted for those mezzes but at least if none are available an exp group can be viable in safer spots with less adds, and without casters needing that crack because they can only cast twice per fight.<br>
<br>
I have suggested this idea to some friends. Some think it's a good idea while some think we need more damage. I don't know if this would work or not but at least it's something different. Verant already tried the &quot;let's give them more damage&quot; idea and it really hasn't made things balanced. Perhaps this idea should be at least tested to see if it can help.<br>
<br>
Failing this idea coming to pass, and if they are going to stick with the critical hit idea for wizards, please make it way more frequent than it is now. In it's current form it's not helping much at all.<br>
<br>
<br>
Juliebar Happytoes<br>
Evoker of the 55th level<br>
Xegony<br>
