<br>
The problem is that tou can consider 3 areas of the game (solo, xp group and raid) and balancing needs to make all classes desirable in all situations.<br>
<br>
Now, the wizard situation:<br>
 - Solo: we are doing fine there. Quad kiting is efficient and Verant does not want to make us better at it. That is understandable.<br>
 - xp group: that is where we have a problem. Our only role in xp groups is to make damage, and we are not very good at it for the common xp groups that spend 45-50 minutes per hour fighting. So that is where wizards need a big boost.<br>
 - Raid: we are one of the best raiding classes. Granted that some &quot;uber&quot; melee can now out damage us on some long encounters. We don't really need a big increase in raid efficiency, more allowing us to compete with high end equipped melee in high end fights.<br>
<br>
So, taking &quot;random&quot; figures (more like educated guess really), we should get no damage output increase for soloing, 50% damage output for xp groups, and variable increase in raids, depending on achievements and specific fight situation.<br>
<br>
Now the problem with higher mana regen is that it is not specifically applied to any of those areas. The solution needs to be a little more customized than that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uizualxev.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Izual Xev</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/27/02 5:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another idea</span><hr size=1> At level 60 i'm 100% sure that i've never been the highest DMG contributor for a non luclin mob without using banes.  i'm probably in the top 10... but when you have 60 melee with primals/epic/or any other uber weapons you realize why you're there...  after the dust settles and the melee loot is dolled out they need to get out right?  TAXI!!   <br>
